Q.

Although q was never extensively employed by the Romans, it certainly was employed commonly, at an early period, in certain words in which it was afterwards supplanted by c. Foremost among these is PEQVNIA, which is written with a q in the great majority of cases in the oldest inscriptions, although, curiously enough, the first example of the word is in 10, where it appears as PECVNIAM.
